ari, E., Lehto, J., Kokkinen, L., Saranummi, N., (2009), www.vtt.fi/files/projects/Innote/systeminnovationsinthemakingi.pdfs, ""System innovation in the making: hybrid actors and the challenge of up-scaling"", paper presented at 2nd Annual Conference of the Health and Care Infrastructure Research and Innovation Centre, Brighton, 2-3 April, available at (accessed 19 May 2010)Kline, S., Rosenberg, N., An overview on innovation (1986) The Positive Sum Strategy, pp. 275-305. , Landau, R., Rosenberg, N. (Eds.), National Academy Press, Washington, DC; Lillrank, P., Kujala, J., Parvinen, P., (2004) Terveydenhuollon Tuotannonohjaus, , Talentum, Helsinki; Linna, P., Pekkola, S., Ukko, J., Melkas, H., Defining and measuring productivity in the public sector: Managerial perceptions (2010) International Journal of Public Sector Management, 23 (3), pp. 300-320; Lundvall, B.-A., Innovation as an interactive process: From user-producer interaction to the national system of innovation (1988) Technical Change and Economic Theory, pp. 349-369. , Dosi, G., Freeman, C., Nelson, R., Silverberg, G., Soete, L. (Eds.), Pinter Publishers, London/New York, NY; Nordgren, L., Value creation in health care services - developing service productivity: Experiences from Sweden (2009) International Journal of Public Sector Management, 22 (2), pp. 114-127; McLaughlin, H., What's in a name. 'Client', 'patient', 'customer', 'consumer', expert by experience', 'service user' - what's next? (2009) British Journal of Social Work, 39 (6), pp. 1101-1117; Moore, M., (1995) Creating Public Value Strategic Management in Government, , Harvard University Press, Cambridge, MA; Moore, M., Hartley, J., Innovations in governance (2008) Public Management Review, 10 (1), pp. 3-20; Nelson, R., Winter, S.G., (1982) An Evolutionary Theory of Economic Change, , Harvard University Press, Cambridge, MA; Niemelä, M., Julkisen sektorin reformin pitkä kaari Valtava-uudistuksesta Paras-hankkeeseen (2008) Sosiaali- Ja Terveysturv