"Hillman K., Nilsson M., Rickne A., Magnusson T.","Fostering sustainable technologies: A framework for analysing the governance of innovation systems",2011,"Science and Public Policy",38,5,,403,415,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-79959887935&partnerID=40&md5=1aa803a05e85e39f4fc2cd843c8bfe16","Department of Building, Energy and Environmental Engineering, University of Gävle, SE-801 76 Gävle, Sweden; Kräftriket 2B, SE-106 91 Stockholm, Sweden; School of Business, Economics and Law, University of Gothenburg, PO Box 625, SE-405 30 Göteborg, Sweden; Department of Management and Engineering, Linköping University, SE-581 83 Linköping, Sweden","Hillman, K., Department of Building, Energy and Environmental Engineering, University of Gävle, SE-801 76 Gävle, Sweden; Nilsson, M., Kräftriket 2B, SE-106 91 Stockholm, Sweden; Rickne, A., School of Business, Economics and Law, University of Gothenburg, PO Box 625, SE-405 30 Göteborg, Sweden; Magnusson, T., Department of Management and Engineering, Linköping University, SE-581 83 Linköping, Sweden","The development and diffusion of technological innovations need governing in order to contribute to societal goals related to sustainability. Yet, there are few systematic studies mapping out what types of governance are deployed and how they influence the development and diffusion of sustainable technological innovations. This paper develops a framework for analysing the role of governance in innovation systems aimed towards sustainability. The framework is based on the literatures on governance, technological innovation systems and socio-technical transitions. We foresee empirical studies based on the framework that may serve as a needed input into governance processes. © Beech Tree Publishing 2011.",,"empirical analysis; governance approach; innovation; sustainability; technological development; technology diffusion",,,,,,"Asheim, B.T., Isaksen, A., Regional innovation systems: The integration of local 'sticky' a