"Suderman J.","Principle-based concepts for the long-term preservation of digital records",2010,"ACM International Conference Proceeding Series",,,,,,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-80054786785&partnerID=40&md5=fd3e083e4459028aea815eba2a7f7e3d","Corporate Information Management Services, City Clerk's Office, City of Toronto, Canada","Suderman, J., Corporate Information Management Services, City Clerk's Office, City of Toronto, Canada","The InterPARES Research Project focuses on preserving digital records so that they remain trustworthy, that is, authentic, reliable, and accurate through time. While not a standards-making body, the Project, directed by Dr. Luciana Duranti and based at the University of British Columbia in Canada, has established meaningful baselines and benchmarks for assessing the authenticity and reliability of records. These tools are applied to preserve or assess the continuing trustworthiness of records as they inevitably pass through technological transitions, whether across systems or jurisdictions or over time. The work focuses on a close association of the record creators with trusted preservers, charged with ensuring that records preserved can be trusted by users. Baselines and benchmarks have been tested in governmental, artistic, and scientific case studies and general studies to establish a framework of principles for the development of policies, strategies and standards for the long-term preservation of digital records. © 2010 ACM.","archival theory; concept of record; digital records; diplomatics; e-government records; electronic art; electronic science; electronic systems",,,,,,,"Official Ford Sync Site, , http://www.fordvehicles.com/innovation/sync/?brand=flm, checked 22 March 2010; http://interpares.org/, website, checked 7 March 2010InterPARES Terminology Database, , http://interpares.org/ip2/ip2_terminology_db.cfm, Unless otherwise stated, all definitions are taken from the checked 20 August 2011; Duranti, L., Suderman, J., Todd, M., Appendix 19: A Framework of Principles for the Development of Policies, Strategies and Standards for the Long-term Preservation of Digital Records (2008) International Research on Permanent Authentic Records in Electronic Systems (InterPARES) 2: Experiential, Interactive and Dynamic Records, , http://www.interpares.org/display_file.cfm?doc=ip2_book_appendix_19.pdf, [electronic version] Luciana Duranti and Randy Preston, eds. Padova, Italy: Associazione Nazionale Archivistica Italiana, website checked 20 August 2011; noteDuranti, L., Thibodeau, K., Appendix 2: The Concept of Record in Interactive, Experiential and Dynamic Environments: The View of InterPARES (2008) International Research on Permanent Authentic Records in Electronic Systems (InterPARES) 2: Experiential, Interactive and Dynamic Records, pp. 59-60. , ""One must distinguish between what is output by the system and the document(s) that enable the system to produce its output. Such documents are 'enabling:' they enable the interactions, experiences or processes the system executes. Provided they are properly maintained and managed as intellectually interrelated parts of records aggregations, enabling documents can be considered records."" [electronic version] Luciana Duranti and Randy Preston, eds. Padova, Italy: Associazione Nazionale Archivistica Italiana; (2006) Archival Science, 6 (1), pp. 13-68. , http://www.interpares.org/display_file.cfm?doc=ip2_book_appendix_02.pdf, First published in website checked 20 August 2011; Tennis, J.T., Preston, R., Part Eight -Terminological Instruments: Terminology Cross-domain Task Force Report (2008) International Research on Permanent Authentic Records in Electronic Systems (InterPARES) 2: Experiential, Interactive and Dynamic Records, p. 9. , http://www.interpares.org/display_file.cfm?doc= ip2_book_part_8_terminology_task_force.pdf, [electronic version] Luciana Duranti and Randy Preston, eds. Padova, Italy: Associazione Nazionale Archivisti