rural areas of India. We focus on the challenges of introducing radical innovations into the residential energy sector in developing countries. For the purpose of this paper the Uttam Urja project is conceptualized as an 'experiment' and analysed using the Strategic Niche Management (SNM) framework. The paper emphasizes that to effect socio-technical transitions to clean energy options on the ground, it is desirable to focus on technology customization and innovative financing to cater to the needs and concerns of end users. © 2010 Elsevier Ltd.","Customization; Leapfrogging; Rural energy; Strategic Niche Management","article; biomass energy; developing country; energy conservation; household; illumination; India; priority journal; residential area; rural area",,,,,,"Ahammed, F., Taufiq, D.A., Applications of solar PV on rural development in Bangladesh (2008) Journal of Rural Community Development, 3 (1), pp. 93-103; Angel, D., Rock, M.T., Environmental rationalities and the development state in East Asia: prospects for a sustainability transition (2009) Technological Forecasting & Social Change, 76 (2), pp. 229-240; (2001) Handbook for Financial & Development Professionals, , http://www.areed.org/training/handbook/index.htm, Africa Rural Energy Enterprise Development (AREED), (Accessed on 1 September 2009); Barnes, D.F., Halpern, J., The role of energy subsidies (2000) Energy and Development Report 2000: Energy Services for the World's Poor, pp. 60-67. , World Bank, Washington, DC, P.J. Brook, S. Smith (Eds.); Benson, S.M., Orr, F.M., Sustainability and energy conversions (2008) MRS Bulletin-Materials Research Society, 33 (4), pp. 297-302; Berkhout, F., Verbong, G., Wieczorek, A., Raven, R., Lebel, L., Bai, X., Sustainability experiments in Asia: innovations shaping alternative development pathways? (2010) Environmental Science and Policy, 13 (4), pp. 261-271; Chaurey, A., Kandpal, T.C., Solar lanterns for domestic lighting in India: viability of central charging s