"Raven R., Van Den Bosch S., Weterings R.","Transitions and strategic niche management: Towards a competence kit for practitioners",2010,"International Journal of Technology Management",51,1,,57,74,,2,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77952415360&partnerID=40&md5=1ae50c8b5c9af34210f2e89b15359105","Eindhoven University of Technology, Department of Technology Management, PO Box 513, 5600 MB Eindhoven, Netherlands; Dutch Research Institute for Transitions, Faculty of Social Sciences, Erasmus University, PO Box 1738, 3000 DR Rotterdam, Netherlands; BU Innovation and Environment TNO, P.O. Box 49, 2600 AA Delft, Netherlands","Raven, R., Eindhoven University of Technology, Department of Technology Management, PO Box 513, 5600 MB Eindhoven, Netherlands; Van Den Bosch, S., Dutch Research Institute for Transitions, Faculty of Social Sciences, Erasmus University, PO Box 1738, 3000 DR Rotterdam, Netherlands; Weterings, R., BU Innovation and Environment TNO, P.O. Box 49, 2600 AA Delft, Netherlands","Structural problems in modern societies, such as climate change and congestion problems, require 'transitions' towards a more susTWNnable fulfilment of social needs. Recent research shows that experimenting in niches is crucial for learning about social challenges and stimulating transitions. Through a series of 'transition experiments' in different niches, social innovations can be improved and eventually replace dominant practice. This article reviews the literature on transitions and strategic niche management and argues that it has a strong analytical core, but less effort has been made to develop a managerial perspective. The authors aim to contribute to such perspective by developing a 'competence kit': a learning module that provides practitioners (e.g., policy makers, companies, intermediary organisations and NGO's) that are involved in transition experiments with an analytical framework, guidelines and tools and recognisable examples. The results from the first workshop with practitioners to explore potential applications of the competence kit are promising. Copyright © 2010 Inderscience Enterprises Ltd.","Competence kit; Experiment; SNM; Strategic niche management; TM; Transition; Transition management","Congestion problem; Learning modules; Policy makers; Potential applications; SNM; Social challenges; Social needs; Strategic niche management; Structural problems; Transition experiment; Transition management; Climate change; Ecology; Management; Traffic congestion; Experiments",,,,,,"Andringa, J., Weterings, R., Competenties van transitieprofessionals (2006) Competentiecentrum Transities, , Utrecht; Astley, W.G., The two ecologies: Population and community perspectives on organisational evoluation (1985) Administrative Science Quarterly, 30, pp. 224-241; Caniëls, M., Romijn, H., Strategic Niche Management as an Operational Tool for Sustainable Innovation: Guidelines for Practice (2006) Schumpeter Conference 2006, , 21-24 June, Nice, France; Cowan, R., Hultén, S., Escaping lock-in: The case of the electric vehicle (1996) Technological Forecasting and Social Change, 53, pp. 61-79; Elzen, B., Geels, F.W., Green, K., (2004) System Innovation and the Transition to Sustainability, , Theory, Evidence and Policy, in Elgar, E. (Ed.), Cheltenham and Northampton; Geels, F.W., Technological transitions as evolutionary reconfiguration processes: A multi-level perspective and a case study (2002) Research Policy, 31 (8-9), pp. 1257-1274; Geels, F.W., Technological transitions and system innovations (2005) A Co-evolutionary and Socio-technical Analysis, , Cheltenham and Northampton: Edward Elgar; Geels, F.W., Raven, R.P.J.M., Non-linearity and expectations in niche-development trajectories: Ups and downs in Dutch biogas development (1973-2003) (2006) Technology Analysis and Strategic Management, 18, pp. 375-392; Grin, J., Weterings, R., Reflexive monitoring of system innovative projects: Strategic nature and relevant competences (2005) Paper presented at IHDP-conference, , Bonn, October 2005; Hoogma, R., Exploiting technological niches (2000) PhD thesis, , Twente University, Enschede; Kemp, R., Loorbach, D., Transition management: A reflexive governance approach (2006) Reflexive Governance for Sustainable Development, pp. 57-81. , in Voß, J.P., Bauknecht, D. and Kemp, R. Eds., Edward Elgar, Cheltenham/Northampton; Kemp, R., Schot, J.W., Hoogma, R., Regime shifts to sustainability through processes of niche formation: The approach of strategic niche management (1998) Technology Analysis and Strategic Management, 10, pp. 175-196; Kemp, R., Van Den Bosch, S., Transitie-experimenten: Praktijkexperimenten met de potentie om bij te dragen aan transities (2006) Kenniscentrum voor Duurzame Systeeminnovatie en Transities (KCT), Delft/Rotterdam; Loeber, A., Inbreken in het gangbare (2003) Transitiemanagement in de Praktijk, , De NIDO-benadering NIDO, Leeuwarden; Loorbach, D., Transition management: New mode of governance for sustainable development, PhD thesis (2007) International Books, , Erasmus University Rotterdam, Utrecht; Lynn, G.S., Morone, J.G., Paulson, A.S., Marketing and discontinuous innovation: The probe and learn process (1996) California Management Review, 38, pp. 8-37; McKelvey, B., Organizational systematics (1982) Taxonomic Lessons from Biology, , University of California Press, Berkeley; Mourik, R., Raven, R.P.J.M., (2006) A Practitioners View on Strategic Niche Management, , ECN-E-06-039, Petten; Mulgan, G., Social innovation: What it is, why it matters and how it can be accelerated (2006) Oxford Said Business School; Nooteboom, S., Adaptive networks. The governance for sustainable developments (2006) Uberon Academic Publishers, Delft; Raven, R.P.J.M., Strategic niche management for biomass (2005) A Comparative Study on the Experimental Introduction of Bioenergy Technologies in the Netherlands and Denmark, , PhD Thesis, Eindhoven University of Technology, Eindhoven; Rip, A., Kemp, R