"Agudelo-Toro A.Y., Velez C.M.","Transition management for the smooth flight of a small autonomous helicopter",2010,"Journal of Intelligent and Robotic Systems: Theory and Applications",58,1,,69,94,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77950371353&partnerID=40&md5=9e2405c74c31fa115684857ccbe43e50","Basic Sciences Department, EAFIT University, Cr 49 No. 7 sur 50, Medellin, Colombia","Agudelo-Toro, A.Y., Basic Sciences Department, EAFIT University, Cr 49 No. 7 sur 50, Medellin, Colombia; Velez, C.M., Basic Sciences Department, EAFIT University, Cr 49 No. 7 sur 50, Medellin, Colombia","This work is centered in the definition of a transition management system for a small autonomous helicopter based on trajectory smoothing and a finite state machine (FSM). A smooth flight schedule decreases transients originated by direction changes and flight mode transitions (e.g., horizontal flight to hover mode). Although previous works have presented trajectory generation and FSM oriented controls, no previous studies have mixed these approaches in a single framework together with speed transitions. The proposed methods are validated in simulation with a realistic dynamic model of a small helicopter. © 2009 Springer Science+Business Media B.V.","Autonomous air vehicle; Helicopter; Robotics; Smooth speed; Trajectory","Autonomous air vehicle; Autonomous air vehicles; Autonomous helicopters; Direction change; Finite state machines; Flight mode transition; Flight schedules; Speed trajectories; Trajectory generation; Transition management; Logic circuits; Robotics; Trajectories; Helicopters",,,,,,"Agudelo-Toro, A., (2008) Trajectory Smoothing and Transition Management for A Small Autonomous Helicopter, , Master's thesis. EAFIT University, Medellin, Colombia; Bartels, R.H., Beatty, J.C., Barsky, B.A., (1987) An Introduction to Splines for Use in Computer Graphics & Geometric Modeling, , Morgan Kaufmann Los Altos 0682.65003; Branicky, M., Borkar, V., Mitter, S., A unified f