"Loorbach D., Rotmans J.","The practice of transition management: Examples and lessons from four distinct cases",2010,"Futures",42,3,,237,246,,7,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77950860744&partnerID=40&md5=7ed8df13fd16f9e4ac10967d5be7c942","Dutch Research Institute For Transitions - Drift, Erasmus University Rotterdam, Burgemeester Oudlaan 50, P.O. Box 1738, 3000 DR, Rotterdam, Netherlands","Loorbach, D., Dutch Research Institute For Transitions - Drift, Erasmus University Rotterdam, Burgemeester Oudlaan 50, P.O. Box 1738, 3000 DR, Rotterdam, Netherlands; Rotmans, J., Dutch Research Institute For Transitions - Drift, Erasmus University Rotterdam, Burgemeester Oudlaan 50, P.O. Box 1738, 3000 DR, Rotterdam, Netherlands","In this article we present four different cases of transition management in which we were involved over the past 10 years. Transition management was developed in the course of this period in theoretical and practical sense, mainly in the Netherlands, as novel mode of governance for sustainable development. The theoretical debate about transition management is being increasingly published, but so far only few empirical examples were. In this article we present four cases that combined give a representative illustration of both the advantages and the difficulties of actually trying to manage transitions. The article ends by drawing lessons and formulating research questions for the future. © 2009 Elsevier Ltd.",,"governance approach; management; sustainable development; technological change; Netherlands",,,,,,"Rotmans, J., Kemp, R., van Asselt, M., Geels, F., Verbong, G., Molendijk, K., (2001) Transitions & Transition management: The Case for a Low Emission Energy Supply, , ICIS, Maastricht; Martens, P., Rotmans, J., Transitions in a globalizing world (2005) Futures, 37, pp. 1133-1144; Loorbach, D., (2007) Transition Management: New Mode of Governance for Sustainable Development, , International Books, Utrecht; Ravetz, J.R., What is 