"Wang E.J., Chen Y.C., Wang W.S., Su T.S.","Analysis of outsourcing cost-effectiveness using a linear programming model with fuzzy multiple goals",2010,"International Journal of Production Research",48,2,,501,523,,1,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-76249109090&partnerID=40&md5=a053218444f26db7d728df1810fc068e","Department of Industrial Management, National Pingtung University of Science and Technology, Pingtung, Taiwan; Department of Industrial Engineering and Management, National Chiao Tung University, 1001 Ta Hsueh Road, Hsinchu 300, Taiwan","Wang, E.J., Department of Industrial Management, National Pingtung University of Science and Technology, Pingtung, Taiwan; Chen, Y.C., Department of Industrial Management, National Pingtung University of Science and Technology, Pingtung, Taiwan; Wang, W.S., Department of Industrial Management, National Pingtung University of Science and Technology, Pingtung, Taiwan; Su, T.S., Department of Industrial Engineering and Management, National Chiao Tung University, 1001 Ta Hsueh Road, Hsinchu 300, Taiwan","This work presents a linear programming model with fuzzy multiple goals for analysing cost effectiveness during vendor selection. The proposed model considers material preparation for outsourcing firms, technological transition, quality, lead time, and their interactions. The model also uses cost, quality and effectiveness as decision criteria for capacity planning and for determining product requirements for multi-stage planning of the make/outsourcing formulation. Different scenarios involving capacity transitions limited by technical factors, additions, and support shortages are mathematically formulated. In addition to its functions for evaluating cost minimisation and for accommodating the components of lead time, quality, and responsiveness, the proposed model also integrates multi-stage functions for supply chain systems. Therefore, the analytical results of this study, regardless of application outcomes or analysis methodology, provide decision criteria for manufacturing firms and introduce a new area of academic research.","Cost effectiveness; Integrated multi-stage model; Outsourcing; Vendor selection","Academic research; Analytical results; Capacity planning; Cost minimisation; Integrated multi-stage model; Leadtime; Linear programming models; Manufacturing firms; Material preparation; Multi-stage; Multi-stage models; Multi-stage planning; Product requirements; Supply chain systems; Technical factors; Technological transition; Vendor Selection; Chains; Cost effectiveness; Costs; Dynamic programming; Industrial research; Linearization; Outsourcing; Supply chain management; Supply chains; Cost benefit analysis",,,,,,"Abdel-Malek, L., Kullpattaranirun, T., Nanthavanij, S., A framework for comparing outsourcing strategies in multi-layered supply chain (2005) International Journal of Production Economics, 97 (3), pp. 318-328; Aissaoui, N., Haouari, M., Hassini, E., Supplier selection and order lot sizing modeling: A review (2007) Computer and Operations Research, 34 (12), pp. 3516-3540; Amid, A., Ghodsypour, S.H., O'Brien, C., Fuzzy multiobjective linear model for supplier selection in a supply chain (2006) International Journal of Production Economics, 104 (2), pp. 394-407; Araz, C., Ozfirat, P.M., Ozkarahan, I., An integrated multicriteria decision-making methodology for outsourcing management (2007) Computers and Operations Research, 34 (12), pp. 3738-3756; Bellman, R.E., Zadeh, L.A., Decision-making in a fuzzy environment (1970) Management Science, 17 (4), pp. 141-164; Bendor, P.S., Improving purchasing productivity at IBM with a normative decision support system (1985) Interfaces, 15 (3), pp. 106-115; Bhutta, K.S., Huq, F., Supplier selection problem: A comparison of the total costs of ownership and analytic al hierarchy process (2002) Supply Chain Management, 7 (3-4), pp. 126-135; Chalos, P., Costing, control, and strategic analysis in outsourcing decisions (1