"Robertson E.M., Alarcon-Rodriguez A.D., Galloway S.J., Ault G.W.","Outline for an integrated multiple energy carrier model of the UK energy infrastructure",2009,"Proceedings of the Universities Power Engineering Conference",,, 5429553,,,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-77951759286&partnerID=40&md5=8fb5aaa9d32f95741e282d60fd392feb","University of Strathclyde, United Kingdom","Robertson, E.M., University of Strathclyde, United Kingdom; Alarcon-Rodriguez, A.D., University of Strathclyde, United Kingdom; Galloway, S.J., University of Strathclyde, United Kingdom; Ault, G.W., University of Strathclyde, United Kingdom","This paper presents an outline for a development stage model of the UK energy infrastructure. The model will use transition pathways as inputs to simulate the UK energy infrastructure toward 2050. Transition pathways are socio technical narratives that are used here to describe possible evolutions of the UK energy industry as it moves towards 2050 and a lower carbon economy. It is the aim of the authors to use an energy infrastructure model - based on the concept of 'energy hubs' proposed elsewhere - to determine the energy infrastructure needed to facilitate the conversions and transfers of energy that will occur as the energy sector in the UK moves towards a lower carbon economy. ©2009 IEEE.","Emissions; Energy hubs; Energy infrastructure; Energy resources; Multiple energy carriers; Power system simulation; Socio technical pathways; Transition pathways","Emissions; Energy carriers; Energy infrastructures; Power system simulations; Sociotechnical; Transition pathway; Energy resources; Electric power systems",,,,,,"(2008) Digest of United Kingdom Energy Statistics, , BERR, Editor; 2008 Seven Year Statement, , National Grid plc; (1998) Kyoto Protocol to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change, , United Nations; Stern, N., (2007) The Economics of Climate Change: The Stern Review, , Cambridge: Cambridge University Press;