"Diez-Martin F., Dominguez-Rodrigo M., Sanchez P., Mabulla A.Z.P., Tarrino A., Barba R., Prendergast M.E., De Luque L.","The middle to later Stone Age technological transition in east africa. New data from mumba rockshelter bed V (Tanzania) and their implications for the origin of modern human behavior",2009,"Journal of African Archaeology",7,2,,147,173,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-75849141108&partnerID=40&md5=265b2b0039ae0e3ac2afc3637023f09b","Department of Prehistory and Archaeology, University of Valladolid, Pza. del Campus s/n, 47011 Valladolid, Spain; Department of Prehistory, Complutense University, Prof. Aranguren s/n, 28040 Madrid, Spain; Archaeology Unit, University of Dar es Salaam, P.O. Box, 35050 Dar es Salaam, Tanzania; Centro Nacional de Investigación sobre la Evolución Humana (CENIEH), Avda. de la Paz 28, 09004 Burgos, Spain; Department of Anthropology, Harvard University, Cambridge, MA 02138, United States; Fundación Conjunto Paleontológico de Teruel, Edificio Dinópolis, Avda. Sagunto s/n, 44002 Teruel, Spain","Diez-Martín, F., Department of Prehistory and Archaeology, University of Valladolid, Pza. del Campus s/n, 47011 Valladolid, Spain; Domínguez-Rodrigo, M., Department of Prehistory, Complutense University, Prof. Aranguren s/n, 28040 Madrid, Spain; Sánchez, P., Department of Prehistory and Archaeology, University of Valladolid, Pza. del Campus s/n, 47011 Valladolid, Spain; Mabulla, A.Z.P., Archaeology Unit, University of Dar es Salaam, P.O. Box, 35050 Dar es Salaam, Tanzania; Tarriño, A., Centro Nacional de Investigación sobre la Evolución Humana (CENIEH), Avda. de la Paz 28, 09004 Burgos, Spain; Barba, R., Department of Prehistory, Complutense University, Prof. Aranguren s/n, 28040 Madrid, Spain; Prendergast, M.E., Department of Anthropology, Harvard University, Cambridge, MA 02138, United States; De Luque, L., Fundación Conjunto Paleontológico de Teruel, Edificio Dinópolis, Avda. Sagunto s/n, 44002 Teruel, Spain","Recent re-excavation of Mumba Rockshelter unearthed an unbiased lithic sample from Bed V. Technological analysis has permitted a reinterpretation of the so-called Mumba Industry, a transitional industry between Middle and Later Stone Ages originally defined by Mehlman (1989). Our data confirm Mehlman S observation that the ""evolutionary"" markers in Mumba Bed V are basically typological. However, our study differs from his in that we classify all of Bed V as LSA based on the combined analyses of typology and technology in our excavated assemblage. From a technological perspective, no changes have been observed throughout the sequence, and continuity is the main technological characteristic of the series. The only transitional marker from Lower through Upper Bed V is the appearance of the geometric crescent in the latter, taking into account that microliths exist throughout the sequence. This evidence casts some doubts on previous interpretations and underscores the need to recover a larger sample using modern excavation techniques. It also stresses the need to define the MSA/LSA transition in better terms, combining techno-typological criteria. © Africa Magna Verlag.","East Africa; Later Stone Age; Lithic technology; Middle Stone Age; Modern human behavior; Mumba rock-shelter; Technological transition",,,,,,,"Ambrose, S.H., Chronology of the Later Stone Age and food production in East Africa (1998) Journal of Archaeological Science, 25 (4), pp. 377-392; Ambrose, S.H., Small things remembered. Origins of early microlithic industries in Sub-Saharan Africa (2002) Thinking Small: Global Perspectives on Microlithization. Archaeological Papers of the American Anthropological Association, 12, pp. 9-29. , Elston, R.G. & Kuhn, S.L. (eds.), Wiley-Blackwell, Hoboken; Baena, J., Tecnología lítica experimental (1998) B.A.R. International Series, 721. , Archaeopress, Oxford; Barham, L., Backed tools in Middle Pleistocene central Africa and their evolutionary significance (2002) Journ