"Wang Z.W., Chen J.","Achieving low-carbon economy by disruptive innovation in China",2008,"Proceedings of the 4th IEEE International Conference on Management of Innovation and Technology, ICMIT",,, 4654448,687,692,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-56749156971&partnerID=40&md5=3802eb43060ca3585fe4dd26b56c1dd5","School of Management, Zhejiang University, Hangzhou, China; China School of Management, Fuzhou University, Fuzhou, China","Wang, Z.W., School of Management, Zhejiang University, Hangzhou, China; Chen, J., China School of Management, Fuzhou University, Fuzhou, China","This paper proposes a framework for China to achieve low-carbon economy by disruptive innovations. China's rapid industrialization and economic growth have significantly increased its energy consumption. The issue of Greenhouse Gas mitigation poses a huge challenge to China to create an innovative and sustainable development pattern. Both theoretical and empirical studies imply that technological transition approach would be a suitable approach to achieve sustainable innovation for low-carbon economy. By analyzing the differences between disruptive innovations and radical innovations, we propose that to trigger technological transition in developing countries like China, disruptive innovations are wiser approaches than radical innovations. Then, we suggest a low-carbon technological transitions model which focuses on fostering disruptive innovations as triggers for low-carbon economy transition. ©2008 IEEE.","Disruptive innovation; Low-carbon economy; Technological transition","Carbon; Developing countries; Economics; Global warming; Greenhouse gases; Planning; Strategic planning; Sustainable development; Carbon economies; Disruptive innovation; Disruptive innovations; Economic growths; Empirical studies; Energy consumption.; Greenhouse gas mitigations; Low-carbon economy; Radical innovations; Technological transition; Innovation",,,,,,"(2002) ENERGY WHITE PAPER: Our energy fu