"Barnat J., Brim L.","Squeeze all the power out of your hardware to verify your software!",2008,"Communications in Computer and Information Science",17 CCIS,,,604,618,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-78649829918&partnerID=40&md5=583c9aadadf85582f857448e26994fe8","Faculty of Informatics, Masaryk University, Brno, Czech Republic","Barnat, J., Faculty of Informatics, Masaryk University, Brno, Czech Republic; Brim, L., Faculty of Informatics, Masaryk University, Brno, Czech Republic","The computer industry is undergoing a paradigm shift. Chip manufacturers are shifting development resources away from single- processor chips to a new generation of multi-processor chips, huge clusters of multi-core workstations are easily accessible everywhere, external memory devices, such as hard disks or solid state disks, are getting more powerful both in terms of capacity and access speed. This fundamental technological shift in core computing architecture will require a fundamental change in how we ensure the quality of software. The key issue is that verification techniques need to undergo a similarly deep technological transition to catch up with the complexity of software designed for the new hardware. In this position paper we would like to advocate the necessity of fully exploiting the power offered by the new computer hardware to make the verification techniques capable of handling next-generation software. © 2008 Springer-Verlag.",,"Chip manufacturers; Computer industry; Computing architecture; Development resources; External memory; Fundamental changes; Hard disks; Key issues; Multi core; Multi-processors; Paradigm shifts; Position papers; Processor chips; Quality of softwares; Technological transition; Verification techniques; Computer hardware; Computer software selection and evaluation; Solid state devices; Verification; Formal methods",,,,,,"Barnat, J., Brim, L., Černá, I., Property Driven Distribution of Nested DFS (2002) Proceedings of the 3rd Inte