"Genus A., Coles A.-M.","Rethinking the multi-level perspective of technological transitions",2008,"Research Policy",37,9,,1436,1445,,18,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-50649125571&partnerID=40&md5=8aa2b6494376be130f1769c2a8cd9397","Newcastle University Business School, University of Newcastle upon Tyne, 2nd Floor, Armstrong Building, Newcastle upon Tyne, NE1 7RU, United Kingdom; Brunel Research into Enterprise, Sustainability and Ethics, School of Business and Management, Uxbridge, UB8 3PH, United Kingdom","Genus, A., Newcastle University Business School, University of Newcastle upon Tyne, 2nd Floor, Armstrong Building, Newcastle upon Tyne, NE1 7RU, United Kingdom; Coles, A.-M., Brunel Research into Enterprise, Sustainability and Ethics, School of Business and Management, Uxbridge, UB8 3PH, United Kingdom","In recent years numerous articles have been published which advocate a multi-level perspective (MLP) for the analysis of long-term technological transitions. This paper reviews current transitions research and considers the limitations of the MLP which need to be addressed to enhance understanding of processes of innovation affecting the transformation of technology and society. The paper suggests ways in which the MLP may be effectively rethought, based on more thoroughgoing application of a co-evolutionary concept of technological transitions. © 2008 Elsevier B.V. All rights reserved.","Multi-level perspective; Technological change; Technology policy; Transition management; Transition theory","Innovation; Technology; Co-evolutionary; Current transitions; Multi-level; Multi-level perspective; Technological change; Technology policy; Transition management; Transition theory; Research",,,,,,"Belz, F.-M., A transition towards sustainability in the Swiss agri-food chain (1970-2000): using and improving the multi-level perspective (2004) System Innovation and the Transition to Sustainability: Theory, Evidence and Policy, pp. 97-113. , Elzen B., G