"Tatoglu E., Demirbag M.","Transition in the age of anxiety: The Turkish case",2008,"Journal of Management Development",27,7,,653,659,,1,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-48549095184&partnerID=40&md5=2d59e6f325ebe6446a28b81b583ab0d9","Bahcesehir University, Istanbul, Turkey; University of Sheffield, Sheffield, United Kingdom","Tatoglu, E., Bahcesehir University, Istanbul, Turkey; Demirbag, M., University of Sheffield, Sheffield, United Kingdom","Purpose - The purpose of this paper is to consider the transformation experience of contemporary Turkey, and to provide an introduction to the special issue and a review of the papers in the JMD special issue. Design/methodology/approach - The paper portrays changes in Turkish business and management practices in recent years. Findings - The paper argues that given the dynamic nature of Turkish economy, change is not an option but a required path for transformation and survival. Turbulence and anxieties, sometimes inevitably, distract or at best re-orient the speed of change and transition. Originality/value - The paper stimulates further work by management scholars to develop new perspectives and research agenda that will advance knowledge of the business and management practices in emerging countries.","Internationalization; Transition management; Turkey",,,,,,,"Demirbag, M., ""The dynamics of foreign-local joint venture formation and performance in Turkey"" (1994), unpublished PhD thesis, University of Bradford, BradfordDemirbag, M., Mirza, H., Weir, D.T.H., ""Dynamics of manufacturing joint ventures in Turkey and the role of industrial groups"" (1995) Management International Review, 35, pp. 35-51; Demirbag, M., Tatoglu, E., Glaister, K., ""Dimensions of European direct investment activity in Turkey: Patterns and prospects"" (2007) International Journal of Emerging Markets, 2 (2), pp. 274-294; (2008) Foreign Trade Statistics, , www.dtm.gov.tr/dtmweb/, DTM Undersecretariat of Foreign Trade, Republic of T