"Loorbach D., Van Der Brugge R., Taanman M.","Governance in the energy transition: Practice of transition management in the Netherlands",2008,"International Journal of Environmental Technology and Management",9,2-3,,294,315,,5,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-46449089787&partnerID=40&md5=d209c1cd7808e5e28db920e2fa859dc0","Dutch Research Institute for Transitions (Drift), Faculty of Social Sciences, Erasmus University Rotterdam, 3000 DR Rotterdam, Netherlands","Loorbach, D., Dutch Research Institute for Transitions (Drift), Faculty of Social Sciences, Erasmus University Rotterdam, 3000 DR Rotterdam, Netherlands; Van Der Brugge, R., Dutch Research Institute for Transitions (Drift), Faculty of Social Sciences, Erasmus University Rotterdam, 3000 DR Rotterdam, Netherlands; Taanman, M., Dutch Research Institute for Transitions (Drift), Faculty of Social Sciences, Erasmus University Rotterdam, 3000 DR Rotterdam, Netherlands","A fundamental transformation of our current energy system in the future is inevitable. To this end, this paper presents a 'fresh' perspective on the Dutch energy field based on transition theory. From this perspective, a number of starting points are suggested for energy transition management in order to influence the speed and direction of the energy transition. In the second part of this paper, these principles are used to reflect upon the way the Dutch Ministry of Economic Affairs is currently applying transition management. As such, this paper itself is part of the ongoing co-production of knowledge between science and policy, that emerged over the past few years in the Netherlands with regard to transition management. Copyright © 2008 Inderscience Enterprises Ltd.","Complexity; Energy transition; Governance; Sustainable development; Transition management","Mathematical transformations; (R ,s ,S) policy; current energy; Economic affairs; Energy fields; energy transitions; In order; Netherlands; Starting points; Transition manage