"Donorfio L.K.M., Healy C.","Teaching an interactive television course on adulthood and aging: Making it happen",2008,"Educational Gerontology",34,6,,531,549,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-45849120656&partnerID=40&md5=88842aa187255b0fd4ca041d1785e275","Department of Human Development and Family Studies, University of Connecticut, Waterbury, CT, United States; Institute for Teaching and Learning, University of Connecticut, Storrs, CT, United States; University of Connecticut, 99 East Main Street, Waterbury, CT 06702, United States","Donorfio, L.K.M., Department of Human Development and Family Studies, University of Connecticut, Waterbury, CT, United States, University of Connecticut, 99 East Main Street, Waterbury, CT 06702, United States; Healy, C., Institute for Teaching and Learning, University of Connecticut, Storrs, CT, United States","This article describes the design, development, and successful implementation of a hybrid distance education course on adulthood and aging. The focus is on the pedagogical and technological transitions made in converting a traditional course into an interactive television course (iTV). The course was taught a total of three times, first as a traditional one-site course and twice as an iTV course delivered to three sites. Details are provided on the development of a core team, design of a teaching platform, unexpected challenges and benefits, and implemented changes. Student feedback and lessons learned are also provided. Copyright © Taylor & Francis Group, LLC.",,,,,,,,"Anderson, L.P., Kent, C.A., The effect of interactive television courses on student satisfaction (2002) Journal of Education for Business, pp. 164-168. , January/February; Bruner, J., Factors motivating and inhibiting faculty in offering their courses via distance education [Electronic version] (2007) Online Journal of Distance Learning Administration, 10 (II), pp. 1-21; Burdick, D.C., Introduction to gerontology: A distance education hybrid 