 Capitalism, socialism and democracy, , Harper and Brothers, New York; (1988) Präventive Umweltpolitik, , Simonis U.E. (Ed), Frankfurt/M, New York; Vogel, D., Is there a race to the bottom? The impact of globalization on national regulatory policies (2001) The Tocqueville Review/La Revue Tocqueville, (1), p. 22; ","Jänicke, M.; Environmental Policy Research Center, Freie Universitaet Berlin, Ihnestrasse 22, D-14195 Berlin, Germany; email: hauptman@zedat.fu-berlin.de",,,,,,,,09596526,,JCROE,10.1016/j.jclepro.2007.02.011,,"English","Journal of Cleaner Production",Article,Scopus
"Crawford M., Kerwin G., Gurung A., Khati D., Jha P., Regmi A.C.","Globalizing beauty: Attitudes toward beauty pageants among Nepali women",2008,"Feminism and Psychology",18,1,,61,86,,2,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-38349074432&partnerID=40&md5=1e454c948202fd96c5eb5b03a87fdce5","Department of Psychology, U-1020, University of Connecticut, Storrs, CT 06269, United States; 42 Robin Hood Dr., Gales Ferry CT 06335, United States; TPO/Nepal (Transcultural PsychosocialOrganization), Kathmandu, Nepal; APT 2A, 1000 Austin Street, Evanson, IL 60202, United States; Unit 7, 10 Julia Street, Ashfield 2131, Sydney, NSW, Australia; Department of Psychology, University of Connecticut, United States; Social Psychology Program, University of Connecticut; Cambridge University, United Kingdom; Saint Francis Hospital, Evanston, IL, United States; University of Technology, Sydney, Australia","Crawford, M., Department of Psychology, U-1020, University of Connecticut, Storrs, CT 06269, United States, Department of Psychology, University of Connecticut, United States; Kerwin, G., Department of Psychology, U-1020, University of Connecticut, Storrs, CT 06269, United States, Social Psychology Program, University of Connecticut; Gurung, A., 42 Robin Hood Dr., Gales Ferry CT 06335, United States, Cambridge University, United Kingdom; Khati, D., TPO/Nepal (Transcultural PsychosocialOrganization), Kathmandu, Nepal; Jha, P., APT 2A, 1000 Austin Street, Evanson, IL 60202, United States, Saint Francis Hospital, Evanston, IL, United States; Regmi, A.C., Unit 7, 10 Julia Street, Ashfield 2131, Sydney, NSW, Australia, University of Technology, Sydney, Australia","A series of focus groups and semi-structured interviews were conducted exploring the beliefs of urban Nepali women about the introduction of beauty pageants to Nepal. This qualitative study examined how the competing pressures of modernization and traditionality impinge on Nepali women who are attempting to both resist patriarchal restrictions and preserve long-established cultural values. The large majority of participants expressed ambivalence toward beauty contests in Nepal. They expressed the belief that beauty pageants can help to empower Nepali women, facilitate progress in Nepal, and present Nepal positively on a global stage. Moreover, participants called for the perceived benefits of pageant participation to be extended to rural, impoverished, and lower caste Nepali women. At the same time, participants expressed reservations about Nepali women being objectified by their participation in these contests, deplored their commercial aspects, and felt that beauty pageants could contribute to the development of body image disturbance. Their ambivalence may reflect their conflicting positioning as middle-class citizens and as women in a developing consumer economy that retains strong patriarchal norms. Their complex and conflicting responses help to elucidate the process of gendered social change in a developing country during a time of rapid societal transition. © 2008 SAGE.","Body image; Modernization; Nationalism; Nepal; Objectification",,,,,,,"Ahmed-Ghosh, H., Writing the Nation on the Beauty Queen's Body: Implications for a ""hindu"" Nation (2003) Meridians, 4, pp. 205-27; Press, A., (2006) 'Miss Nevada Katie Rees Fired over Raunchy Photos, , http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,237897,00.html, 2007; Banet-Weiser, S., (1999) The Most Beautiful Girl in the World: Beauty Pageants and National Identity, , Berkeley, CA: University of California Press; (1996) Beauty Contest in Bangalore: Crony Capitalism on Catwalk, , http://www.cpiml.org/liberation/year_1996/october/feature.htm, Bangalore Unit of AIPWA, Campaign against Miss World Beauty Contest 2007; Botta, R., Television Images and Adolescent Body Image Disturbance (1999) Journal of Communications, 47, pp. 22-41; Browne, M., Of All Things: All the Rage in Nepal (2004) Financial Times, , http://search.ft.com/nonFtArticle?id=04082