 dynamics of bubbles and golden ages (2002), Cheltenham: Edward ElgarPestre, D., Thirty years of science studies: Knowledge, society and the political (2004) History and Technology, 20 (4), pp. 351-369; (1980) Middle Range Theory and the Study of Organizations, , Pinder, C.C., and L.F. Moore, eds. Boston: Martinus Nijhoff; Poole, M.S., Van de Ven, A.H., Towards a general theory of innovation processes (1989) Research on the Management of Innovation: The Minnesota Studies, pp. 637-662. , In edited by A.H. Van de Ven, H.L. Angle, and M.S. Poole, New York: Harper & Row Publishers; Rip, A., Kemp, R., Technological change (1998) Human Choice and Climate Change, 2, pp. 327-399. , In edited by S. Rayner and E.L. Malone, Columbus, OH: Battelle Press; Russell, S., The social construction of artifacts: A response to Pinch and Bijker (1986) Social Studies of Science 16, 16 (2), pp. 331-346; Schot, J.W., The usefulness of evolutionary models for explaining innovation. The case of the Netherlands in the nineteenth century (1998) History of Technology, 14, pp. 173-200; Van Driel, H., Schot, J., Radical innovation as a multi-level process: Introducing floating grain elevators in the port of Rotterdam (2005) Technology and Culture, 46 (1), pp. 51-76; Van Lente, H., Rip, A., Expectations in technological developments: An example of prospective structures to be filled in by agency (1998) Getting New Technologies Together, pp. 195-220. , In: edited by C. Disco and B.J.R. van der Meulen, Berlin and New York: Walter de Gruyter; Weick, K.E., Theory construction as disciplined reflexivity: Tradeoff in the 90s (1999) Academy of Management Review, 24 (4), pp. 797-806; Williams, R., Edge, D., The social shaping of technology (1996) Research Policy, 25 (6), pp. 865-899; Woolgar, S., What happened to provocation in science and technology studies? (2004) History and Technology, 20 (4), pp. 339-349","Geels, F.W.; Eindhoven University of Technology, Eindhoven, Netherlands",,,,,,,,01622439,,,10.11