"Geels F.W.","Analysing the breakthrough of rock 'n' roll (1930-1970) Multi-regime interaction and reconfiguration in the multi-level perspective",2007,"Technological Forecasting and Social Change",74,8,,1411,1431,,7,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34548304566&partnerID=40&md5=05e719f6cbc0419edd8d24e5e5b412e6","Eindhoven University of Technology, IPO 2.10, PO Box 217, 5600 MB Eindhoven, Netherlands","Geels, F.W., Eindhoven University of Technology, IPO 2.10, PO Box 217, 5600 MB Eindhoven, Netherlands","The breakthrough of rock 'n' roll was part of broader transformations in the American music industry, involving changes in music instruments, music recording technology, audiences, radio programming and music styles. These transformations will be analysed as sociotechnical transition, using the multi-level perspective. One characteristic of the case is interactions between multiple regimes: radio and recording. Another characteristic is the presence of strong cultural components, with rock 'n' roll as proxy. These characteristics lead to theoretical adjustments in the multi-level perspective. Further analysis also suggests a particular transition path of reconfiguration, in which multiple niche-innovations cumulatively transform the regime. © 2006 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.","Multi-level perspective; Music industry; Reconfiguration; Rock 'n' roll; Transition","Innovation; Musical instruments; Social aspects; Multi-level perspective; Sociotechnical transistion; Technology transfer; media role; music; radio; technological change",,,,,,"Freeman, C., Perez, C., Structural crisis of adjustment, business cycles and investment behaviour (1988) Technical Change and Economic Theory, pp. 38-66. , Dosi G., Freeman C., Nelson R., Silverberg G., and Soete L. (Eds), Pinter, London; Tushman, M., Anderson, P., Technological discontinuities and organization environments (1986) Adm. Sci. Q., 31, pp. 439-465; Christensen, C., (1997) The Innovator's Dilemma: W