"Bhattacharyya S.C.","Energy sector management issues: An overview",2007,"International Journal of Energy Sector Management",1,1,,13,33,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-34547136199&partnerID=40&md5=7c727a8e8391a7b56f589de890ceeb57","Centre for Energy, Petroleum and Mineral Law and Policy, University of Dundee, Dundee, United Kingdom","Bhattacharyya, S.C., Centre for Energy, Petroleum and Mineral Law and Policy, University of Dundee, Dundee, United Kingdom","Purpose - The objective of the paper is to put the energy sector challenges in perspective and to provide a general understanding of sector management issues. Design/methodology/approach - The paper follows an analytic-deductive method to analyse the issues using existing literature as the source of information. Starting with an analysis of the evolution of the sector, the paper identifies various present and future challenges facing the sector and indicates the management issues that could emerge. Findings - As future developments are shaped by the past and present, it is important to identify and understand the drivers that could bring profound changes. The dynamic nature of the sector brings new challenges and a better understanding of the present issues could help prepare for the future. Research limitations/implications - The paper focuses on the broad, generic coverage of the issues and is not intended to provide country specific or industry specific issues and challenges. Originality/value - The paper presents the multi-dimensional interactions of the energy sector and offers an analysis of the multitude of sector management issues.","Energy industry; Transition management","Analytic-deductive method; Enegry industry; Energy sector management; Energy management; Industrial economics; Sustainable development; Industrial management",,,,,,"Bielecki, J., ""Energy security: Is the wolf at the door?"" (2002) The Quarterly Review of Economics and Finance, 42, pp. 235-250; Davis, G.A., Tilton,