"Hezri A.A.","Utilisation of sustainability indicators and impact through policy learning in the Malaysian policy processes",2005,"Journal of Environmental Assessment Policy and Management",7,4,,575,595,,5,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-31144436767&partnerID=40&md5=a15823bd9c99331cc39667e449f3737c","Center for Resource and Environmental Studies, The Australian National University, Canberra, ACT 0200, Australia; Institute for Environment and Development (Lestari), Universiti Kebangasaan Malaysia, 43600 Bandar Baru Bangi, Selangor, Malaysia","Hezri, A.A., Center for Resource and Environmental Studies, The Australian National University, Canberra, ACT 0200, Australia, Institute for Environment and Development (Lestari), Universiti Kebangasaan Malaysia, 43600 Bandar Baru Bangi, Selangor, Malaysia","It is axiomatic that indicator systems are indispensable in informing the societal transition toward sustainability. However, our understanding of how sustainability indicators systems are linked to policy systems and processes is still limited. Using a 'policy orientation' as an analytical strategy, we investigate the processes surrounding the creation, diffusion, dissemination, and utilisation of sustainability indicators at the national scale of policy-making. Utilising an empirical case study of Malaysia, this paper seeks to answer two questions: How are indicators currently used in policy systems; and, have sustainability indicators had policy impacts in the past? The latter is addressed using policy learning as a frame of analysis. © Imperial College Press.","Indicator utilisation; Malaysia; Policy learning; Sustainability indicators","environmental impact assessment; environmental policy; learning; sustainability; Asia; Eurasia; Malaysia; Southeast Asia",,,,,,"Aiken, S.R., Leigh, C.H., Leinbach, T.R., Moss, M.R., (1982) Development and Environment in Peninsular Malaysia, , Singapore: McGraw Hill International; Bell, S., Morse, S., (2003) Measuring 