), pictures of research for political change"" (2000) Management Learning, 31 (1), pp. 51-65; Irigaray, L., (1985) Speculum of the Other Woman, , Porter, C. (transl.) (Ed.), Cornell University Press, Ithaca, NY; Kay, R., ""Liberation from emancipation? Changing discourses of women's employment in soviet and post-Soviet Russia"" (2001) Journal of Communist Studies and Transition Politics, 18, pp. 51-71. , March; Khotkina, Z.A., ""Gendernyi podkod k analizu truda I zanyatosti"" (2002) Gendernyi Kaleidoskop, , Malysheva, M.M. (Ed.) Academia, Moscow; Linz, S.J., ""Gender differences in the Russian labour market"" (1996) Journal of Economic Issues, 30 (1), pp. 161-186; Mesli, V.L., Miller, A.H., ""The gender bias of institutional support in Lithuania"" (1993) Ukraine and Russia, Europe-Asia Studies, 45 (3), pp. 505-533; Metcalfe, B.D., Linstead, A., ""Gendering teamwork: Rewriting the feminine"" (2003) Gender Work and Organization, 19 (1), pp. 94-119; Monousava, G., ""Gender differentiation and industrial relations"" (1996) Conflict and Change in the Russian Industrial Enterprise, , Clarke, S. (Ed.) Edward Elgar, Cheltenham; Musson, G., (2004) Life-histories, Essential Guide to Qualitative Methods in Organisation Research, , Sage, London; Puffer, S.M., (1996) Business and Management in Russia, , (Ed.) Edward Elgar, Brookfield, WI; Rich, A., (1994) Of Women Born: Motherhood As Experience and Institution, , Cambridge University Press, Cambridge; Riess, N., (1995) Russian Talk: Culture and Conversation During Perestroika, , Cornell University Press, New York, NY; Rosener, J., ""Ways women lead"" (1990) Harvard Business Review, pp. 119-125. , November-December; Rubchak, M.J., ""In search of a model: Evolution of feminist consciousness in Ukraine and Russia"" (2001) European Journal of Women's Studies, 8 (2), pp. 149-160; Rzhanitsyna, L., ""Working women in Russia at the end of the 90s"" (2000) Problems of Economic Transition, 43 (7), pp. 68-86; Sätre Ählander, A., ""Women an