"Magnusson T., Tell F., Watson J.","From CoPS to mass production? Capabilities and innovation in power generation equipment manufacturing",2005,"Industrial and Corporate Change",14,1,,1,26,,7,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-14344261654&partnerID=40&md5=bd21f1622af7240e694dad4e8f520229","Department of Management/Economics, Linköping University, SE-581 83 Linköping, Sweden","Magnusson, T., Department of Management/Economics, Linköping University, SE-581 83 Linköping, Sweden; Tell, F.; Watson, J.","This article presents a case study of small, distributed electrical power generators, representing a potential substitute for large power plants, and raises questions regarding the ability of established manufacturers to manage this kind of technological transition. The analysis demonstrates that the step from experimental R&D to commercial production is particularly difficult for the incumbents. This observation is explained by showing that whereas manufacturing of large power plants rests upon extensive systems integration capabilities, distributed generators are based on a 'plug-and-play' logic. © ICC Association 2005; all rights reserved.",,"manufacturing; power plant; research and development",,,,,,"Acha, V., Davies, A., Hobday, M., Salter, A., 'Exploring the capital goods economy: Complex product systems in the UK' (2004) Industrial and Corporate Change, 13 (3), pp. 505-529; Anderson, C., 'Anläggningsprojekt och organisatoriskt lärande' (1998), Licentiate Thesis, Linköping University, LinköpingArora, A., Fosfuri, A., Gambardella, A., (2001) Markets for Technologies, , MIT Press: Cambridge, MA; (2001) Submission to the Cabinet Office Energy Review, , BG Group 7th September; Breschi, S., Lissoni, F., Malerba, F., 'Knowledge proximity and technological diversification' (1998), mimeo, CESPRI/Università BocconiBrusoni, S., Prencipe, A., 'Unpacking the black box of modularity: Technologies, products and organisations' (2001) Industrial and Corporate Chang