"Karlstrom M., Hulten P., Bagge L.","Preliminary assessment of a fuel cell public transport system for a medium-sized city in the year 2020",2004,"Advances in Transport",16,,,617,626,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-4644224185&partnerID=40&md5=b4ec202a928d092ed858d4b91ac2e778","Environmental Systems Analysis, Chalmers University of Technology, Gothenburg, Sweden; Infrastructure/Urban Studies, Royal Institute of Technology, Stockholm, Sweden; Infrastructure, Royal Institute of Technology, Stockholm, Sweden","Karlström, M., Environmental Systems Analysis, Chalmers University of Technology, Gothenburg, Sweden; Hultén, P., Infrastructure/Urban Studies, Royal Institute of Technology, Stockholm, Sweden; Bagge, L., Infrastructure, Royal Institute of Technology, Stockholm, Sweden","A preliminary assessment of the description of a system made in fuel cells in a medium-sized city is presented. The consequences of introducing a fuel cell public transport system in a fictitious medium sized city in Europe, Excity is also discussed. A route system is designed for a light rail or a guided bus system, both of them using modularly designed 12 meter fuel cell vehicles. It is concluded that the reduction of carbon dioxide emissions from the increased rider-ship in the local public transport system proposed full use is not large, but might fulfil the goals of 2020.","Fuel cell; Hydrogen; Public transport; Transition management","Carbon dioxide; Electricity; Energy utilization; Gas emissions; Hydrogen; Land use; Risks; Transportation; Public transport; Stock capacity; Transition management; Urban transport system; Fuel cells",,,,,,"Hydrogen energy and fuel cells a vision for our future (2003) Tech. Report, , EU high level group for hydrogen and fuel cells; National hydrogen energy roadmap - Production, delivery, storage, conversion, application, public education and outreach (2002) Tech. Report, , United States Department of Energy; Moving to a hydrogen economy: Dr