"Skalen P.","New public management reform and the construction of organizational identities",2004,"International Journal of Public Sector Management",17,2-3,,251,263,,19,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-2042533498&partnerID=40&md5=c7caa90afed591d9c781ce8ba4131feb","Service Research Center, Karlstad University, Karlstad, Sweden","Skålén, P., Service Research Center, Karlstad University, Karlstad, Sweden","An underlying and fundamental aim of the new public management (NPM) reform program is to transform the organizational identity of public organizations into a business-like identity. In this paper the construction of organizational identity as an effect of NPM initiatives is analyzed from a sensemaking perspective. The study draws on data from a two-and-a-half-year study of the introduction of NPM at the public health care authority in the region of Värmland in Sweden. It is concluded that NPM creates heterogeneous, conflicting and fluid organizational identities rather than the uniform and stable business identity it is supposed to. © Emerald Group Publishing Limited.","Health services sector; Organizational culture; Public sector reform; Transition management","health care; public sector; reform process; Eurasia; Europe; Northern Europe; Scandinavia; Sweden; Varmland",,,,,,"Abbott, A., (1988) The System of Professions: an Essay on the Division of Expert Labor, , The University of Chicago Press, Chicago, IL and London; Albert, S., Whetten, D.A., Organizational identity (1985) Research in Organizational Behavior, , Cummings, L.L. and Staw, B.M. (Eds) JAI Press, Greenwich, CT; Brunsson, N., Hägg, I., (1992) Marknadens Makt, , SNS, Stockholm; Brunsson, N., Olsen, J.P., (1997) The Reforming Organization, , Fagbokforlaget, Bergen; Christensen, T., Lægreid, P., A transformative perspective on administrative reforms (2001) New Public Management: The Transformation of Ideas and Practice, , Christensen, T. and Lægreid, P. (Eds) Ashgate, Aldershot; DiMaggi