"Mauhler M.G.","Exposure time, the aura, and telerobotics [Ekspozicijski čas, avra in telerobotika]",2002,"Filozofski Vestnik",23,3,,113,120+224,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-61249263173&partnerID=40&md5=7454fcf8d2d2b5a5f9b14b087a4a5af0",,"Mauhler, M.G.","This text focuses on the notions of exposure time and the photographic aura in the context of Internet telerobotics. It examines the aesthetic, political, artistic, and epistemological impact of the technological transition from an exposure lasting several hours to only a fraction of a second, which for Walter Benjamin marked the gradual evaporation of »aura« from the image. Current limitations of telerobotic technology today - delays in transmission-time, busy signals from service providers, crashing web browsers - can be seen as restoring the aura, and with it our sense of space and time.","Epistemology; Exposure time; Telerobotics; The aura",,,,,,,"Benjamin, W., Mala zgodovina fotografije, prev (1998) Alenka Mercina, v: Izbrani spisi, Studia humanitatis, pp. 87-111. , Ljubljana, str; Benjamin, W., Umetnina v času, ko jo je mogoče tehnično reproducirati, prev (1998) Janez Večko, v: Izbrani spisi, Studia humanitatis, pp. 147-176. , Ljubljana, str; Benjamin, Mala zgodovina fotografije, p. 97; Rodowick, D.N., (1997) Gilles Deleuze's Time Machine, Duke University Press, Durham in London, pp. 8-9; Renger-Patzsch, A., (1928) Die Welt is Schön, , ur. Carl Georg Heise, Kurt Wolff Verlag, München; Albert Renger-Patzsch: Photographer of Objectivity (1998) Jurgen Wilde, , Za novejšo objavo Renger-Patzschevih fotografij glej Ann in MIT Press, Cambridge, Massachusetts; Benjamin, W., The Author as Producer, v: Charles Harrison in Paul Wood (ur.) (1992) Art in Theory 1900-1990, pp. 486-487. , Blackwell, Oxford in Cambridge, str; Formenti, C., (1991) La guerra senza nemici, p. 29; Baudrillard, C., Zalivska vojna se ni zgodila (1991) Liberation, 4. , Pariz, januar; Peter Weibel, C., Ways of Contextualisati