"Vollenbroek F.A.","Sustainable development and the challenge of innovation",2002,"Journal of Cleaner Production",10,3,,215,223,,18,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0036604715&partnerID=40&md5=163888ae6af96a417367807698d1c348","Department of Strategy, Ministry of Environment, PO Box 30945, 2500 GX The Hague, Netherlands","Vollenbroek, F.A., Department of Strategy, Ministry of Environment, PO Box 30945, 2500 GX The Hague, Netherlands","Innovation does not automatically lead to societal progress, as is implicitly assumed in technology push-oriented policies. This assumption is an inheritance of the Enlightenment; i.e., the belief that science will automatically lead to a better quality of life. The strive for sustainable development needs an approach towards innovation that can be characterised as society pull: the society has to decide which (balance of) economical, ecological and social goals are to be met. Society pull can be organised by developing shared perspectives for the future, which are inspiring for public and private policy-makers and investors. In this paper this is worked out as transition management: a process approach directing innovation towards sustainable development. A crucial aspect of transition management is that innovation is no longer driven by the past, but attracted by the future. © 2002 Elsevier Science Ltd. All rights reserved.","Innovation; Sustainable development; Transition management","Industrial management; Productivity; Societies and institutions; Strategic planning; Transition management; Sustainable development",,,,,,"(1998) Policy Document on Environment and Economy, , Ministry of Environment, Den Haag; Vollenbroek, F.A., Weterings, R.A.P.M., Butter, M., Technology options for sustainable development (1998) OECD Proceedings of the Budapest Workshop: Technology Foresight and Sustainable Development, , 11 December; Weterings, R.A.P.M., Kuijper, J., Smeets, E., Arnokkée, G.J., Minne, B., (1997) 81 options, technology for sustainable development, , Report by TNO/STB, Delft; Heilbroner, R.L., (1986) The worldly philosophers, , New York: Simon and Schuster; Tijmes, P., Sacraliteit en schaarste. De dubbele huishouding van de mimese (1996) Het labyrint van verlangen, , Girard R., editor. Agora: Pelckmans, in Dutch; (1999) Keys for sustainable development: Energy, biodiversity and space, , The Hague: Dutch Ministry of Environment; Weaver, P., Jansen, L., Van Grootveld, G., Van Spiegel, E., Vergragt, P., (2000) Sustainable technology development, , Sheffield: Greenleaf Publishing; Te Riele, H.R.M., Duifhuizen, S.A.M., Hötte, M., Zijlstra, G., Sengers, M.A.G., (2000) Kunnen drie mensen de wereld doen omslaan? Are three individuals able to change the world?, , Report by Twynstra Gudde. The Hague: Ministry of Environment; in Dutch; Van saneren naar innoveren, Report by the Dutch Ministry of Environment, Den Haag 2000 [in Dutch]Kemp, R., Schot, J., Hoogma, R., Regime shifts to sustainability through processes of niche formation. The approach of strategic niche management (1998) Technol. Anal. Strategic Manag., 10, pp. 175-195; Rotmans, J., Kemp, R., Van Asselt, M., Geels, F., Verbong, G., Molendijk, K., (2000) Transities and transitie-management, , Report. Maastricht: International Centre for Integrative Studies (ICIS), University of Maastricht; Kuijjer, H.H., From environmental management towards sustainable entrepreneurship (1999) International environmental management benchmarks, , Hitchens D.M.W.N., Clausen J., Fichter K., editors. Berlin: Springer; Ashford, N., Government and environmental innovation in Europe and North America Environmental transformation, governance, and globalization, , Sonnenfeld D.A., Mol A.P.J., editors. special issue. American Behavioral Scientist, in press; Keynes, J.M., Economic possibilities for our grandchildren (1986) The not idly philosophers, , Heilbroner R.L., editor. New York: Simon and Schuster","Vollenbroek, F.A.; Department of Strategy, Ministry