"Rice Mark P., Leifer Richard, O'Connor Gina","Managing the transition of a discontinuous innovation project to operational status",2000,"IEEE International Engineering Management Conference",,,,586,590,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0033714929&partnerID=40&md5=faf45c2b47c91c650ac3750cc410ac1b","Rensselaer Polytechnic Inst, Troy, United States","Rice, Mark P., Rensselaer Polytechnic Inst, Troy, United States; Leifer, Richard, Rensselaer Polytechnic Inst, Troy, United States; O'Connor, Gina, Rensselaer Polytechnic Inst, Troy, United States","Longitudinal data collected from twelve discontinuous innovation projects over 5 years in 10 large, mature firms reveal the challenges of managing the surprisingly difficult transition from R&D project to an operating unit. In these twelve projects a substantial `readiness gap' existed between the project teams and the receiving business units, leading us to propose the formation of a formal transition team as an organizational response for bridging this gap. The transition team and the organization's associated management structure must answer twelve critical questions before a project can be successfully transitioned. Based on an analysis of transition practices, we identify seven keys to improving the effectiveness of transition management.",,"Data reduction; Economic and social effects; Product development; Discontinuous innovations; Transition managements; Research and development management",,,,,,,"Rice, Mark P.; Rensselaer Polytechnic Inst, Troy, United States",,"Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers;Engineering Management Society","IEEE, Piscataway, NJ, United States","2000 IEEE International Engineering Management Conference","13 August 2000 through 15 August 2000","Albuquerque, NM, USA",57549,,,IEMCF,,,"English","IEEE International Engineering Management Conference",Conference Paper,Scopus
