"Makarovic B.","Detailed photogrammetric digital mapping in the context of GIS",1996,"ITC Journal",,3-4,,284,299,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0030368088&partnerID=40&md5=6aaa6d124fc40d686de26f2b8d009d10","Department of Photogrammetry, ITC, Rekkenbrink 79, 7544 LB Enschede, Netherlands","Makarovic, B., Department of Photogrammetry, ITC, Rekkenbrink 79, 7544 LB Enschede, Netherlands","In the present societal transition from industrial to information era, the need for diverse, detailed, current and accurate information is increasing. This enhances the impact of photogrammetry on detailed digital mapping from large-scale images. Mapping techniques imply different methods and means. Photogrammetric methods can be image-based or stereomodel-based, whereas the means can be analytical or digital (analogue is not addressed here). The methods and means can be further differentiated according to full or primary and differential mapping. A mapping procedure is a model of an existing or newly designed process in the context of a given or anticipated project and production environment. It includes all functions, including those to be performed manually. Attention is focused on the engineering of photogrammetric digital mapping projects, in particular on the GIS context, product specifications, networks of GISs, information structures, production techniques and procedures, quality control, and integration.",,"digital mapping; GIS; photogrammetry",,,,,,"Adolfi, T.P.C., Stephens, P., Definition of remote sensing (1993) PE&RS, 59 (5), pp. 611-613; Elassal, A.A., Photogrammetric open systems (1990) Proc ISPRS Comm II Symp, 28 (2), pp. 322-326. , Dresden, Germany; Leatherdale, J., Specification for mapping at scales between 1-1000 and 1:10000 (2nd edit) (1988) Proc ISPRS Cong, 27 B4, pp. 125-140. , Kyoto, Japan, Comm IV; Makarovic, B., Digital mono plotting (1973) ITC J 1973-4, pp. 583-600; Makarovic, B., Structures for GI and their application in selective sam