"Palmer James D., Runyan Harry M.","NATIONAL GOAL FORMATION IN A TIME OF TRANSITION.",1972,"IEEE Transactions on Systems, Man and Cybernetics",SMC-2,5,,589,594,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0015430968&partnerID=40&md5=f540346cbbe003bdfaa55eb8a9cf030c",,"Palmer, James D.; Runyan, Harry M.","Transition management approach to resolving the issues of value differences in times of discontinuous change is based on the premise that solutions to problems during transition can be attained effectively only if value differences are made explicit. The major elements in the management of discontinuous change require skills in supportive confrontation and conceptual mapping. These skills lead to making values explicit and then to the development of new insights and value relationships. This leads to the cognitive reformation of previously held value patterns and to emergent solutions to otherwise insoluble conflicts.",,"SYSTEMS SCIENCE AND CYBERNETICS; TECHNOLOGY",,,,,,,"Palmer, James D.",,,,,,,,00189472,,ISYMA,,,,"IEEE Transactions on Systems, Man and Cybernetics",,Scopus


